FBIS4-56661 "drlat089_b_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-089 Daily Report 6 May 1994 Barbados Haiti Aristide Asks For Renewal of UN/OAS Mandate Aristide Asks For Renewal of UN/OAS Mandate FL0605191894 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1045 GMT 6 May 94 FL0605191894 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole French BFN [Text] Jean-Bertrand Aristide solicits the renewal of the mandate of the civilian mission in Haiti. In a letter addressed to the UN secretary general, the Haitian president-in-exile asked for the renewal of the mandate of the International Civilian Mission in Haiti, according to the terms of reference already negotiated with Dante Caputo. Referring to a deterioration of human rights and democracy in Haiti, Aristide hoped that the presence of the mission is contributing to an improvement in the human rights situation and helping create a favorable environment for political dialogue in the country.
